Paper: hep-th/9409168

Date: 1994-09-27

Title: On the Nonperturbative Consistency of $d=2$ String Theory

Authors: Joseph Polchinski

Comments: 10 pages, 2 figures, LaTeX (author's name added)

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev.Lett. 74 (1995) 638-641

An infinite number of distinct $d=1$ matrix models reproduce the perturbationtheory of $d=2$ string theory. Due to constraints of causality, however, weargue that none of the existing constructions gives a consistentnonperturbative definition of the $d=2$ string.